cs.CR, cs.SE, cs.SI, cs.PL, cs.CY 

This paper investigates changes over time in the behavior of Android ad libraries, specifically focusing on the permissions used by these libraries. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), as the paper discusses the risks to user privacy and security posed by certain permissions. 

The paper also involves software engineering aspects, such as extracting and classifying ad libraries, estimating release dates, and building a chronological map. Therefore, cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also a likely category. 

The paper also touches on topics related to social implications of technology (cs.SI), programming languages (cs.PL), and cybernetics (cs.CY), as it discusses the impact of ad libraries on user privacy and security, and the use of permissions in programming languages. However, these categories are less likely than cs.CR and cs.SE.
